[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    513[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    514[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | AWS Service | Role |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    515[0m:[38;5;10m[49m |------------|------|
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    516[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon Bedrock** | LLM for orchestration and conversational response generation in retrieval-and-citation mode; embedding model for the per-trial IRB-approved corpora, the recruitment FAQ corpus, and the conversation-history index |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    517[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon Bedrock Agents** | Tool orchestration: define recruitment tools as action groups, manage the multi-step LLM-and-tool flow, preserve tool-call traces as part of the IRB-grade conversation record |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    518[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon Bedrock Knowledge Bases** | Managed RAG over (a) per-trial IRB-approved corpus with strict per-trial isolation via metadata filtering, (b) recruitment FAQ corpus, (c) conversation-history retrieval index. Metadata-filtered retrieval (trial_id, content_type, language, reading_level, IRB-approval-version, effective-date) |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    519[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon OpenSearch Serverless** | Vector and lexical retrieval index backing each Knowledge Base |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    520[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon Bedrock Guardrails** | Content filtering for diagnosis-attempted, treatment-recommendation-attempted, prescription-attempted, trial-recommendation-attempted, comparison-of-trials-as-recommendation, informed-consent-attempted, novel-recruitment-language-generation-attempted (the assistant retrieves; it does not generate trial-specific language) |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    521[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **AWS Lambda** | Chat handler, input/output safety, identity-referral-and-trial-context loading, recruitment tools (trial_state_retrieve, trial_content_retrieve, faq_retrieve, eligibility_evaluate, prescreen_capture, coordinator_handoff_schedule, alternative_trial_search, escalation_propose, demographic_capture, conversation_audit), trial-onboarding workflow steps, recruitment-funnel reporting workers |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    522[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **AWS Step Functions** | Trial-onboarding workflow (content authoring, IRB review, eligibility-rule encoding, FAQ population, coordinator-team training, post-launch monitoring activation), IRB-amendment-deployment workflow |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    523[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon API Gateway** | Public-facing chat endpoint for web, app, SMS, voice, and kiosk channels |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    524[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **AWS WAF** | Rate limiting, bot detection, common attack patterns, recruitment-campaign-traffic-spike accommodations |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    525[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon DynamoDB** | trial-registry, trial-content-version-registry, eligibility-rule-registry, prescreen-store, conversation-state, conversation-metadata, tool-call-ledger, coordinator-handoff-queue, recruitment-decision-record-journal, consent-and-disclosure-record, representativeness-instrumentation-store |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    526[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon S3** | Per-trial IRB-approved corpus archive, conversation archive, recruitment-decision-record journal, per-trial regulatory-artifact archive |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    527[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **AWS HealthLake (optional)** | FHIR-native chart-context retrieval where the recruitment plan includes EHR-prescreen-flag pathways and the patient has IRB-approved consent for the data use |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    528[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **AWS KMS** | Customer-managed encryption keys per data class, with per-trial keys for blast-radius containment between trials and separate keys for the recruitment-decision-record journal and the representativeness-instrumentation store |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    529[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **AWS Secrets Manager** | Credentials for ClinicalTrials.gov listing-management API access (where applicable), sponsor-side recruitment-tracking endpoints, EHR FHIR endpoints (where applicable), and coordinator-team workflow systems |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    530[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon CloudWatch** | Operational metrics (per-trial recruitment funnel, prescreen-completion rate, qualified-handoff rate, coordinator-handoff-accept rate, citation-coverage rate, scope-violation rate, per-cohort slices); alarms |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    531[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **AWS CloudTrail** | API-level audit logging |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    532[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon EventBridge** | Recruitment-event bus (conversation_started, prescreen_completed, eligibility_determined, coordinator_handoff_scheduled, coordinator_handoff_accepted, coordinator_handoff_aged_out, alternative_trial_offered, conversation_closed, IRB_amendment_applied, trial_paused, trial_closed) |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    533[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon Pinpoint** | Coordinator-callback confirmation and reminder messaging; (where the recruitment plan includes proactive outreach) invitation messages to EHR-flagged prospects with TCPA and 10DLC compliance |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    534[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon Connect** | Warm-handoff queue for research coordinators (chat and voice), with prescreen summary and conversation context attached |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    535[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon Kinesis Data Firehose** | Streaming audit and telemetry delivery |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    536[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **AWS Glue Data Catalog + Amazon Athena** | SQL access to audit, decision-record, representativeness, and telemetry data |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    537[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon Comprehend Medical (optional)** | Medical NER over patient-reported text for matching against the eligibility-evaluation tool's input schema |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    538[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon SageMaker (optional)** | Hosted custom eligibility-evaluation classifiers with IRB-reviewed validation evidence and named clinical-leadership ownership |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    539[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon QuickSight** | Per-trial recruitment-funnel and representativeness dashboards with per-cohort slices |
