[49m[38;5;10m+    1317[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1318[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1319[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Variations and Extensions
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1320[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1321[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Decentralized-trial recruitment with home-visit logistics integration.** A variant for trials whose visits are conducted at home or via telehealth rather than at a site. The recruitment conversation includes home-visit logistics language (visit windows, equipment delivery, technical-support availability), the coordinator-handoff includes home-visit scheduling, and the geographic-eligibility evaluation expands to the trial's decentralized catchment.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1322[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1323[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Pediatric-trial recruitment with parental-permission-and-pediatric-assent flows.** A variant for trials enrolling minors. The primary recruitment-conversation participant is the parent or legal guardian; pediatric assent is captured per the IRB-approved age-appropriate process; the architecture's identity model distinguishes parent-as-decision-maker from child-as-assent-giver; the IRB-approved content and eligibility evaluation are pediatric-specific.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1324[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1325[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Surrogate-decision-maker-trial recruitment.** A variant for trials enrolling cognitively-impaired adults, where the legally-authorized representative is the primary recruitment-conversation participant. The architectural extension is the surrogate-identity model with state-specific surrogate-authority documentation and the IRB-approved surrogate-consent process.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1326[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1327[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **EHR-prescreen-flag-driven proactive recruitment.** Where the institution operates an EHR-driven prescreen-flag program (the EHR identifies potentially-eligible patients based on structured criteria), the platform supports invitation messaging via Pinpoint to flagged patients (with the IRB-approved invitation language and the appropriate opt-in mechanics), routing patients who engage to the recruitment conversation with the EHR-flag context attached. The architectural extension is the EHR-prescreen-flag pathway with consent-aware messaging.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1328[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1329[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Sponsor-funded recruitment-campaign integration.** Where the trial sponsor is funding social-media or search ads driving prospective participants to the institution's recruitment platform, the platform tracks per-campaign attribution, applies per-campaign IRB-approved landing-page content, and reports per-campaign funnel metrics back to the sponsor. The architectural extension is the sponsor-attribution layer with per-campaign instrumentation.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1330[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1331[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Multi-language recruitment with validated translations beyond English plus Spanish.** The platform operates natively in the institution's patient-population languages from day one. Per-trial-language-combination IRB review. Native-speaker review of every patient-facing language asset. Per-language launch-gate. Critical for trials whose target population includes substantial non-English-language speakers.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1332[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1333[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Cross-institutional recruitment federation.** A regional or national capability shared across institutions, with each institution contributing its own per-trial IRB-approved content (where federated IRB review permits), its own coordinator queues, and its own audit pipelines. The architectural extension is the federation layer, with per-institution per-trial isolation preserved through to each institution's audit pipeline.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1334[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1335[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Trial-discovery-and-routing capability for the patient unsure which trial is right.** A variant where the patient is not entering with a specific trial in mind but is exploring open trials in their condition. The platform offers trial-discovery information at the institutional-trial-portfolio level (without comparison-as-recommendation framing), and routes the patient into the trial-specific recruitment conversation for any specific trial they want to learn about. The architectural extension is the trial-discovery-and-routing layer with explicit institutional-policy review of the comparison-vs-information framing.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1336[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1337[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Clinician-side recruitment-support tooling.** The platform serves treating clinicians at the point of care with information about open trials their patient may be a candidate for, with the clinician-side tooling integrated into the EHR or a clinician-facing app. The clinician's referral routes the patient to the recruitment conversationalist with the clinician-referral context attached. The architectural extension is the clinician-side surface with EHR or clinician-app integration.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1338[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1339[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Voice-channel recruitment for patients without smartphone or web access.** Voice-first recruitment conversations through Connect plus the institution's research-recruitment IVR, with ASR/TTS layered on the conversational core. Voice-specific design includes slower pacing, explicit confirmation of high-stakes inputs, and tighter latency budgets.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1340[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1341[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Care-navigation overlay for prospective participants who face barriers to trial participation.** When a patient qualifies for a trial but faces barriers (transportation, childcare, lost wages, language access, technology access), the platform connects to the institution's research-care-navigation team for support, working within the IRB-approved framework for participant-burden mitigation.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1342[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1343[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Outcome-correlation pipeline through to consent and randomization.** The platform's effect on consented and randomized enrollments is the substantive outcome metric. The outcome-correlation pipeline integrates with the institution's clinical-trial management system (CTMS) and the sponsor's randomization tracking to produce per-cohort outcome metrics across the full recruitment funnel. The architectural extension is the CTMS integration with per-cohort outcome rollup.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1344[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1345[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Continuous-improvement loop with structured failure-mode labeling.** A structured labeling program where reviewers (research coordinators, clinical leadership, regulatory operations) tag failure modes (under-screening, over-screening, IRB-language-deviation, scope-violation, citation-gap, equity-disparity). The labels feed the per-trial content-revision workflow, the eligibility-rule-revision workflow, and the prompt-tuning workflow.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1346[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1347[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Federated patient-identity-aware multi-trial recruitment.** A variant where the patient interacts with the platform across multiple trial inquiries over time, with cross-trial conversation history (per the institution's IRB-approved data-use plan) preserved to avoid re-asking baseline information. The architectural extension is the longitudinal patient-identity layer with multi-trial conversation-history retrieval.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1348[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1349[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Patient-advocate-reviewed recruitment-language assets.** A variant where the institutional patient-advocate consultants are formal participants in the recruitment-language authoring process, with their input documented as part of the IRB-approved content review. Particularly valuable for trials in conditions affecting populations with documented historical reasons to mistrust clinical research.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1350[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1351[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1352[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1353[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Related Recipes
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1354[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1355[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 11.1 (FAQ Chatbot):** Same chapter, foundational. The recruitment conversationalist inherits the input-screening pipeline, scope filtering, conversation logging, audit pattern, persona discipline, and per-cohort monitoring.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1356[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 11.2 (Appointment Scheduling Bot):** Same chapter. The coordinator-handoff scheduling for warm callbacks builds on the appointment-scheduling pattern.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1357[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 11.4 (Pre-Visit Intake Bot):** Same chapter. The intake bot collects structured data feeding scheduled-visit clinicians; the recruitment bot collects structured data feeding the research coordinator. The two bots share question patterns and prescreen-capture tools.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1358[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 11.5 (Insurance Benefits Navigator):** Same chapter. Patients in recruitment conversations sometimes ask about how trial participation interacts with their insurance coverage; the benefits navigator's plan-document corpus and regulatory-disclosure framework parallel the recruitment platform's IRB-approved-content corpus and IRB-disclosure framework.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1359[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 11.6 (Symptom Checker / Triage Bot):** Same chapter. The continuous-emergency-screening pipeline pattern is shared; recruitment conversations route acute emergencies to the triage pathway.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1360[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 11.7 (Chronic Disease Management Coach):** Same chapter. Patients with chronic conditions enrolled in coaching may be candidates for trials in their condition; the coach can route patients to the recruitment platform with the chronic-disease context preserved.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1361[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 11.8 (Mental Health Support Bot):** Same chapter. The mental-health-crisis routing pattern is shared; recruitment conversations route mental-health crisis disclosures to the mental-health pathway.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1362[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 11.9 (Care Coordination Assistant):** Same chapter. The care-coordination assistant's coordinator-handoff orchestration pattern is closely related to the recruitment conversationalist's coordinator-handoff orchestration pattern.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1363[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 1.4 (Prior Auth Document Processing):** Chapter 1. Trial participation sometimes requires prior authorization for the patient's existing care to continue alongside trial procedures.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1364[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 2.6 (Clinical Note Summarization):** Chapter 2. The chart-context retrieval (where used) may be powered by clinical-note summarization for richer context.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1365[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 2.9 (Clinical Decision Support Synthesis):** Chapter 2. Clinician-side trial-eligibility decision support at the point of care is a parallel pattern; the architectural patterns share concepts.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1366[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 4.7 (Care Management Program Enrollment):** Chapter 4. The pattern of moving patients through a structured pre-engagement workflow is shared.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1367[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 5.7 (Longitudinal Patient Matching):** Chapter 5. The multi-trial longitudinal-patient-identity variation benefits from longitudinal patient matching.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1368[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 6.3 (Treatment Cohort Discovery):** Chapter 6. Cohort discovery and trial recruitment are closely related capabilities; the recruitment platform's per-cohort representativeness instrumentation is informed by cohort-discovery analytics.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1369[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 7.6 (Clinical Trial Eligibility Prediction):** Chapter 7. Trial-eligibility prediction is a parallel capability operating on EHR data; the predicted-eligibility output may feed the recruitment platform's invitation pipeline.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1370[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 10.5 (Patient-Facing Voice Assistant):** Chapter 10. The voice-channel recruitment variation builds on the voice assistant's ASR/TTS patterns.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1371[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 13.x (Knowledge Graphs):** Chapter 13. The institutional trial portfolio may be modeled as a knowledge graph for richer cross-trial querying and for trial-discovery-and-routing capabilities.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1372[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Recipe 14.x (Optimization):** Chapter 14. The coordinator-queue capacity-aware throttling pattern is an instance of resource-allocation optimization.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1373[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
